@page "/big/{N:long}"

@* `:long` -> BigInt (decision 112, applied to a route parameter). 9007199254740993 is one past 2^53:
   a JS number CANNOT hold it and would render ...992. The URL in Home.razor is that exact value, so the
   rendered text is the measurement -- a number-backed converter shows the wrong digit. *@
<div id="page"><h2 id="where">big</h2><span id="n">@N</span><a id="to-home" href="/">home</a></div>

@code {
    [Parameter] public long N { get; set; }
}
